{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5caa5552-687b-42e0-bf2b-08e7e2c1e252","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the summary:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — ❌ Not supported. .NET Core 3.1 is EOL.\n- **`net5.0`** — ❌ Not supported. .NET 5.0 is EOL.\n- **`net462`** — ✅ Supported (.NET Framework ≥ 4.6.2 is fine).\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for the .NET (Core) side.\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n1. Replace `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` with supported TFMs (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`).\n2. Replace the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` references with the single **`MSTest`** meta-package (v3.x).\n\n**Other breaking changes to watch for:**\n- Some assertion APIs have behavioral changes (e.g., `Assert.AreEqual` with floating-point tolerance).\n- Class/Assembly `Initialize`/`Cleanup` lifecycle ordering changes.\n- `DataRow` attribute now requires compile-time constants more strictly.\n\nIf you must keep `netcoreapp3.1` or `net5.0` targets, you'll need to stay on MSTest v2.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"334c1487-6844-4c6d-986b-c76d531e2a66","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Let me think about what I know:\n\n- MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET 6 or .NET Framework 4.6.2. Wait, let me think more carefully.\n- MSTest v3 (the MSTest meta-package starting from 3.x) dropped support for:\n  - .NET 5.0 (which is out of support)\n  - .NET Core 3.1 (which is out of support)\n\nSo MSTest v3 only supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and .NET 6.0 or later. That means `net462` would work fine, but both `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` are incompatible with MSTest v3. Also, MSTest v3 consolidates the framework into a single `MSTest` package rather than separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages. The main compatibility issues are that `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` are no longer supported.\n\nBeyond the framework targeting, there are some breaking changes in MSTest v3 itself—assertion behavior has shifted, `Assert.ThrowsException` works differently, the class cleanup and initialization lifecycle has changed, and `DeploymentItem` attribute behavior is different too.","outputTokens":858,"requestId":"5C24:C4D03:445936:560B38:69F562FA"},"id":"9e8ea65b-82f8-420a-bf0e-9523ca22979d","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:35:54.391Z","parentId":"a31c18f0-46a2-40b6-89a4-28d6bdbd4925"}
